dfischer.utils

Class TextLineTokenExtractorItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.TextLineTokenExtractorItem

  • public class TextLineTokenExtractorItem
extends java.lang.Object
    Extracts form a response content a string token (variable). First the response content is processed line by line by searching a text pattern. Thereafter the string token will be extracted on a line which is relative addressed by the line where the matching text pattern was found.
    See Also:
    TextLineTokenExtractor

    • Constructor Detail

      • TextLineTokenExtractorItem

        public TextLineTokenExtractorItem(int searchPatternPosition,
                          java.lang.String searchPattern,
                          int varExtractLineOffset,
                          java.lang.String delimiterChars,
                          int tokenNumber)
        Creates a new text line token extractor.
        Parameters:
        searchPatternPosition - Location within a single text line where the search pattern will be searched. Possible values are LINE_STARTS_WITH_PATTERN, LINE_CONTAINS_PATTERN, LINE_ENDS_WITH_PATTERN.
        searchPattern - Text patteren which is searched over all text lines.
        varExtractLineOffset - Relative line offset from which line the result token will be extracted after the text pattern was found. Negative as well as positive values are supported. 0 (zero) means the current line where the search pattern was found.
        delimiterChars - List of token delimiter characters (same as used in java.util.StringTokenizer). Delimiter characters themselves will not be treated as tokens.
        tokenNumber - Number/counter of the text token which should be extracted. The first token has the number of 1 (one), not 0 (zero)!
        See Also:
        TextLineTokenExtractor.addTokenExtractorItem(dfischer.utils.TextLineTokenExtractorItem)
